<p id="Par19">To include a Reward or a Punishment policy, let us follow ref.
 <sup>
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR12">12</xref>
 </sup> and consider a group budget 
 <italic>N</italic>∙
 <italic>δ</italic> which can be used to implement any type of policy. The fraction of 
 <italic>N</italic>∙
 <italic>δ</italic> applied to Reward is represented by the weight 
 <italic>w</italic>, with 
 <italic>0</italic> ≤ 
 <italic>w</italic> ≤ 1. Parameters 
 <italic>a</italic> and 
 <italic>b</italic> correspond to the efficiency of Reward and Punishment (for all Figures above it was assumed that 
 <italic>a</italic> = 
 <italic>b</italic> = 1).
